commentPreTextItems.html: They crossed and Boje will face the final ball

commentTextItems.html: paddle sweep taking it on the full to the vacant fine leg boundry and West Indies celebrate a deserved victory

commentPostTextItems.html: A great win from the West Indies after a poor start and then a wonderful innings by Lara ably supported by the rest of the middle order to post a formidable 278
South Africa started well but it was their poor disipline in the field that cost them this match after exceeding the time and being fine an over for it
In the end they were just 4 short of a win but more than likely could have cruised it had there been the 6 extra balls
To be fair the West Indies dominated the middle portion of the innings with Captain Hooper doing brilliantly to marshal a team that really was a bowler light
He missed a trick but packing the legside field and having his spinners fire it in at Klusener's leg stump
But it was he who was out on the mid wicket boundary to take the catch that say the back of Klusener and effectively seal the win
If this is anything to go by we can expect a wonderful tournament
